# The services/controllers function descriptions here

# NOT FINISHED YET

# EnemyService:
    void Sync(Player player) - sends current enemies in the game to the specific player (client).
    void SpawnEnemy(string name, CFrame startCF?, boolean spawnAsBoss?, number currentNodeIndex?, number, nextNodeIndex) - spawns an enemy specified by name, and then sends it to the all clients to render its model.
    void DestroyEnemy(table enemy) - destroys an enemy, optionally, if enemy have an EnemyModule, calls from this module a :OnDeath() method wrapped in the task.spawn.
    void OnHeartbeat(number dt) - loops through all enemies in the game and calculates a new enemy position, then sends updated data about enemies to the all clients.
    void ClearAll() - destroys all enemies in the game, internally uses EnemyService:DestroyEnemy().
    table GetEnemies() - returns all enemies in the game.
    table GetEnemiesUseArray() - returns all enemies in the game, but returns it in an array form instead of dictionary.

# TowerService:
    void Sync(Player player) - loops through all towers in the game and sends all data about towers to the specified player.
    void AddPlayerTowers(Player player, typedef table struct towerStruct) - adds a structure to the player towers data, equipped towers, skins, owned towers.
    void TryUpgrade(Player player, string id) - tries to upgrade a tower, uses UpgradeHandler:tryUpgrade() internally.
    void ChangeTarget(Player player, string towerId) - changes a target of the tower, tower is retrived through towerId parameter.
    void PlaceTower(Player player, string name, table vectors) - tries to place tower, on the raycast result position if placing successed
    void SellTower(Player player, string id) - tries to sell tower, if successfull, returns a total cost divided by 3
    void OnHeartbeat(number dt) - iterates through all towers in the game and then sends all data about towers to the all clients
    void OnStepped(number dt) - iterates through all towers in the game AND THEN if tower have :Attack() method, it calls it. Different from other firerate implementations, but this prevents firerate bugs/clock drifts.
    table GetPlayerTowers(Player player) - returns all player towers data, even skins, owned towers, etc.
    
